# Jibon - Smart Electric Scooter Rides A modern, full-stack electric scooter rental website inspired by Zypp, featuring a dark theme with yellow accents. ## Features ### Frontend - Modern, responsive design with dark theme and yellow accents - Smooth scrolling and animations - Interactive signup form with validation - Pricing calculator - Mobile-friendly navigation - Performance optimized with lazy loading ### Backend (Optional) - Node.js and Express server - MongoDB database integration - RESTful API endpoints - User management system - Ride tracking functionality ## Project Structure ``` jibon-website/ ├── index.html # Main HTML file ├── style.css # Custom CSS styles ├── script.js # Frontend JavaScript ├── server.js # Backend server (Node.js/Express) ├── package.json # Node.js dependencies └── README.md # This file ``` ## Setup Instructions ### Frontend Only (Static Website) 1. Simply open `index.html` in a web browser 2. All CSS and JavaScript are included via CDN ### Full Stack Setup (with Backend) #### Prerequisites - Node.js (v14 or higher) - MongoDB (local or cloud instance) #### Installation Steps 1. **Clone or download the project files** ```bash mkdir jibon-website cd jibon-website ``` 2. **Install dependencies** ```bash npm install ``` 3. **Set up MongoDB** - Install MongoDB locally or use a cloud service like MongoDB Atlas - Update the connection string in `server.js` if needed 4. **Start the server** ```bash npm start ``` For development with auto-reload: ```bash npm run dev ``` 5. **Access the website** - Open your browser and navigate to `http://localhost:3000` ## API Endpoints ### User Management - `POST /api/signup` - Create new user account - `GET /api/users` - Get all users (admin) - `GET /api/users/:id` - Get user by ID - `PUT /api/users/:id` - Update user profile ### Pricing & Rides - `GET /api/pricing` - Get pricing plans - `POST /api/calculate-ride` - Calculate ride cost - `POST /api/users/:id/rides` - Record completed ride ### Utility - `GET /api/health` - Health check endpoint - `POST /api/contact` - Contact form submission - `POST /api/newsletter` - Newsletter subscription ## Design Specifications ### Color Scheme - Primary Background: `#0A0A0A` (Dark) - Secondary Background: `#1A1A1A` (Gray) - Accent Color: `#FFD700` (Yellow) - Text Colors: White, Gray, Yellow ### Typography - Primary Font: Poppins (Google Fonts) - Font Weights: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700, 800 ### Responsive Breakpoints - Mobile: < 640px - Tablet: 640px - 1024px - Desktop: > 1024px ## Features in Detail ### 1. Hero Section - Animated yellow scooter image - Call-to-action buttons - Statistics counter animation ### 2. How It Works - Step-by-step guide with icons - Interactive animations ### 3. Pricing Plans - Three-tier pricing structure - Hover effects and animations - Popular plan highlighting ### 4. Signup Form - Real-time validation - Success/error messages - Credit assignment simulation ### 5. Mobile Responsiveness - Hamburger menu for mobile - Responsive grid layouts - Touch-friendly buttons ## Deployment ### Option 1: Static Hosting (Frontend Only) - Netlify - Vercel - GitHub Pages - AWS S3 ### Option 2: Full Stack Hosting - Heroku - DigitalOcean - AWS EC2 - Google Cloud Run ## Environment Variables Create a `.env` file for production: ```env PORT=3000 MONGODB_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string NODE_ENV=production ``` ## Browser Support - Chrome (latest) - Firefox (latest) - Safari (latest) - Edge (latest) ## Performance Optimizations - Lazy loading for images - Minified CSS and JavaScript (via CDN) - Efficient animations using CSS transforms - Proper caching headers ## Security Features - Input validation and sanitization - CORS configuration - Rate limiting (to be implemented) - HTTPS enforcement (in production) ## Contributing 1. Fork the repository 2. Create a feature branch 3. Commit your changes 4. Push to the branch 5. Create a Pull Request ## License MIT License - see LICENSE file for details ## Contact For support or inquiries: - Email: support@jibon.com - Phone: +91 1800-123-4567 - Website: https://jibon.com --- **Note:** This is a demonstration project. For production use, additional security measures, payment integration, and real-time features would be required.